title: Incredible McCray vintage refrigerator
description: This one will take that special person or situation, but we think it's the "coolest" and most notable piece we've ever had.  It's a LARGE vintage McCray Refrigerator that dates to around 1915-1920.  These were the days when food/meat was kept cold by inserting large blocks of ice in the bottom area.  It's McCray model #96 which was used both in homes and businesses. It's all original, including the hardware and latches.  The McCray Company was located in Kendallville, IN and has a rich history:   https://towns-and-nature.blogspot.com/2017/09/kendallville-in-mccray-refrigerator.html.    It's 79" tall, 34" deep, and 64" wide.  It also weighs about 700 lbs and is solid oak.  If you have a BIG home and a BIG kitchen with a floor that could support the weight, this would be incredible.  It could also go in a large family room or a big garage man-cave.  For a restaurant or brew pub, it would also be incredible.  Not very many of these left around!  We can't deliver it.  It will take a fork loader and a flat bed trailer.  That's how we got it into the barn shop.
